e supernatural media virus to negotiate as well as actively shape imaginations of the network society and the dangers of a globalized, technologized world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGothic fiction (Literary genre)y20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGothic fiction (Literary genre)y21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSupernatural in literature. 0aSupernatural in motion pictures. 0aViruses in literature. 0aViruses in motion pictures. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aBritish Studies. 4aFilm. 4aHorror. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aMedia. 4aNetwork Society. 4aVirus. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican Studies.  aBritish Studies.  aFilm.  aHorror.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMedia.  aNetwork Society.  aVirus.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z97831107673150 cprintz978383765559940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839455593?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839455593zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839455593/origina